                            <comment id="13986289" author="cheolsoo" created="Thu, 1 May 2014 02:37:52 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patches. I&apos;ll run unit tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13986291" author="cheolsoo" created="Thu, 1 May 2014 02:43:42 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;While updating the code, I also made the following change regarding &lt;tt&gt;MULTI_INPUTS_RECORD_COUNTER&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;MULTI_STORE_RECORD_COUNTER&lt;/tt&gt;-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;from&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
Counter counter = reporter.getCounter(group, name);
counter.increment(1);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;to&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
reporter.incrCounter(group, name, 1);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13986915" author="cheolsoo" created="Thu, 1 May 2014 20:41:27 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;RB link-&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/20973&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/20973&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13986920" author="rohini" created="Thu, 1 May 2014 20:43:55 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Few comments:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Can we make the below one an abstract method T getContext() in TaskContext?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; FetchContext get() {
+        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; context;
+    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) transient to be added to private String counterName = null; in POStore.java&lt;br/&gt;
3) getMultiStoreCounterName() can return null. So remove (name == null) check might cause NPE.&lt;br/&gt;
4) reporter != null checks have been removed. Is that ok? Is it never expected to be null?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13987196" author="rohini" created="Fri, 2 May 2014 01:01:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13987233" author="cheolsoo" created="Fri, 2 May 2014 02:09:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk and tez branch. Thank you Rohini for reviewing it!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
